HEADWORD: Epanody
<hw>E*pan"o*dy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Epanodos</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The abnormal change of
an irregular flower to a regular form; -- considered by evolutionists to
be a reversion to an ancestral condition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

